President Obama received a briefing on the earthquake in Japan and the tsunami warnings across the Pacific. Senior US government officials, including Homeland Security Secretary Janet Napolitano and Federal Emergency Management Agency Administrator Craig Fugate, provided an update on the situation and the actions being taken to assist affected states and territories in the US. The government is closely monitoring the situation and remains in contact and coordination with state and local officials. The public is urged to listen to instructions from state and local officials and stay updated through NOAA Weather Radio and local news.